* BMAP extended literals: character literals and the LITORG pool flush.
*   =HABCDEF -> 6 BCD chars (A=021..F=026) = 212223242526
*   =4AWXYZ  -> 4 ASCII chars W=0127 X=0130 Y=0131 Z=0132 = 127130131132
*   =5       -> 000000000005
*   LIT (LITORG) flushes the pool, so the =5 AFTER it is a SEPARATE word
*   (no dedup across the flush): the LITERALS section gets 5 twice.
       OUNAME XLIT
       LDQ    =HABCDEF
       STA    =4AWXYZ
       LDA    =5
       LIT
       ADA    =5
       END
